Subject: PATCH: pws-20: manual corrections
Date: Wed, 02 Jun 1999 13:38:20 +0200
From: Peter Stephenson <pws@ibmth.df.unipi.it>

This is mainly some corrections to the orthography in some bits of the
manual I know about (parameter expansion and zftp functions), where the
lack of quotes became more obvious in info after my patch on the subject.
It should make things a bit more consistent than they were before, at any
rate.  My major rule was that quotes were put in if it was clearer with
them, and conversely.  (Using words like `orthography' is a sign I'm not
having much fun.)  There are also a few mistakes corrected.

Unfortunately something nasty is happening with nofill() in info.  I took
to writing like this,
 nofill(line1 ...)
 nofill(line2 ...)
because multiline nofill's were having dire effects in manual pages.
However, now they are getting filled in info, so this may not have been
the right way.

